CartridgeProperties.Cheats:
To play the hidden game in Vecmania, start a new game of Patriots, score 150 points, then press pause.

Thank you message

On the Birds of Prey title screen, press down, then right on the controller. "Special Bonus" will appear at the bottom of the screen. Press up to see a special thank you message from creator John Dondzila.&#x20;

CartridgeProperties.Eastereggs:
&#x20;   The original Rockaroids was a limited edition game, then it appeared on All Good Things. The rockaroids on this version, for the most part, move a lot faster than on the original.
    Rockaroids Remix was originally sold on the Vectrex carts web site, not Classic Game Creations. However, once John Dondzila took over Vectrex carts from Mark Shaker, it became available on his site until the end of 2013, once Dondzila could not spare the time to create games and work his day job any more. However, Packrat Video Games, LLC re-released the game in April, 2015.
    The ship’s design from this game is repeated on Rockaroids Remix: Third Rock on Vecmania.&#x20;

&#x20;    Hyperchase is one of the initial 12 games released worldwide for the Vectrex.
    While there were only two racing games originally released for the Vectrex, Hyperchase preceded Pole Position by a couple of months.
    Hyperchase is one of only two original games which utilized the analog control capabilities of the Vectrex. The other is game two of Star Hawk.&#x20;

· HIDDEN MESSAGE: Before your man stops flashing when you kill your last man, press and hold 1+3+4. When the "GOT YOU HUMANOID" summary screen appears with your score, the programmer's initials will appear in the lower right corner – “CMK” (for Chris King). This screen will stay for about 90 seconds before going back to the game select screen.  There’s no way to back out of it. {Pete Rittwage and Fred Taft}

· 2 versions exist!  Early production carts had a bug in it (described below), which was fixed in a revised version (called Berzerk II in-house - see picture).

· BUG: Get to a screen with a lot of robots and continuously fire down a long corridor.  If too much “action” is happening at once, the game will glitch out, and the score counter will either become garbled or disappear (in rare cases the screen may even go “blank” for a few seconds).  At this point, exit the maze.  On the next screen, if you check your score you should have received anywhere from 100,000 to 800,000 points, or extra humanoids, or BOTH!  Note- if the trick works, the game will probably be running at a much harder level.
